(420, 3, '2017-05-17 13:22:45', '2017-05-17 07:52:45', 'No new program has been started by the BJP government for modernisation of madrasas. Scheme for Providing Quality Education in Madrasas (SPQEM) has been running <a href="http://mhrd.gov.in/sites/upload_files/mhrd/files/lu1717.pdf">since 2008-2009</a>. The scheme is a demand driven scheme and expenditure depend on proposals from the state governments. Spending for SPQEM in 2015-16 increased to Rs 294 crore from Rs 108 crore in 2014-15. The number of madrasas covered under the scheme has gone up from 15,000 in 2013-14 to 21,000 in 2015-16.\r\n\r\nHowever, with around <a href="http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/3ts-to-encourage-madrassas-to-teach-regular-subjects-too/articleshow/57821271.cms">70,000 madrasas</a> in the country, only 30% are being covered under SPQEM. No information could be found about the spending and number of madrasas covered from 2016-17.', 'Start a national modernization program for madrasas', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'start-a-national-modernization-program-for-madrasas', '', '', '2017-05-17 13:22:45', '2017-05-17 07:52:45', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=420', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
