(426, 3, '2017-05-17 13:23:16', '2017-05-17 07:53:16', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">The BJP government. has launched the</span> <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=138891"><span style="font-weight: 400;">pilot of e-NAM</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> - the </span><a href="http://www.enam.gov.in/NAM/home/index.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">e-trading platform</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> for the National Agriculture Market, </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">as a first step towards creating a single National Agricultural Market. </span><a href="http://www.enam.gov.in/NAM/home/mandis.html#"><span style="font-weight: 400;">250 markets </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">have been linked to the portal against the target of 220 by March 2017.</span>\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">With the aim of creating a single barrier-free market across India, the NITI Ayog </span><a href="http://agriexchange.apeda.gov.in/news/Newssearch.aspx?newsid=24745"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">rolled out the draft</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> on the model Agricultural Produce Market Committee (APMC)</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">The draft was put for public and stakeholder review, welcoming  comments and suggestions  till March 15, 2017.</span>', 'Evolve a single ''National Agriculture Market''', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'evolve-a-single-national-agriculture-market', '', '', '2017-05-17 13:23:16', '2017-05-17 07:53:16', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=426', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
(427, 3, '2017-05-17 13:23:41', '2017-05-17 07:53:41', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">On 13th May 2016, the cabinet approved the </span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=145338"><span style="font-weight: 400;">National Intellectual Property Rights (IPR) Policy</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. It is a vision statement which aims to create synergies across different components in the IPR sector. While the IPR policy is balanced, but real progress will depend on whether it is supported by legislative reforms or not. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The BJP government also revised the Start-Up Intellectual Property Protection </span><a href="http://ipspectra.ztmbpd.iari.res.in/Acts%20and%20Ruels/Policy/SIPP%20Scheme.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">(SIPP)</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> scheme and made</span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=123202"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> patent filing</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> process online, cost effective and transparent.  Patent filings </span><a href="http://www.ipindia.nic.in/writereaddata/Portal/IPOAnnualReport/1_71_1_Annual_Report_2015-16_English__2_.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">increased by 10%</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> in the fiscal 2015-16.</span>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.livemint.com/Politics/jEaTS5ZzyoyTBXNWWXHSbP/Over-1-lakh-patents-filed-since-2013.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Indian patent data</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> shows that a massive 73% of the patents here are filed by foreigners and foreign entities, and only 27% ,by Indians/ Indian entities. </span>', 'Will embark on the path of IPRs and Patents in a big way', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'will-embark-on-the-path-of-iprs-and-patents-in-a-big-way', '', '', '2017-05-18 18:09:09', '2017-05-18 12:39:09', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=427', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
(428, 3, '2017-05-17 13:22:45', '2017-05-17 07:52:45', 'No new program has been started by the BJP government for modernisation of madrasas. Scheme for Providing Quality Education in Madrasas (SPQEM) has been running <a href="http://mhrd.gov.in/sites/upload_files/mhrd/files/lu1717.pdf">since 2008-2009</a>. The scheme is a demand driven scheme and expenditure depend on proposals from the state governments. Spending for SPQEM in 2015-16 increased to Rs 294 crore from Rs 108 crore in 2014-15. The number of madrasas covered under the scheme has gone up from 15,000 in 2013-14 to 21,000 in 2015-16.\r\n\r\nHowever, with around <a href="http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/3ts-to-encourage-madrassas-to-teach-regular-subjects-too/articleshow/57821271.cms">70,000 madrasas</a> in the country, only 30% are being covered under SPQEM. No information could be found about the spending and number of madrasas covered from 2016-17.', 'Start a national modernization program for madrasas', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '420-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-17 13:22:45', '2017-05-17 07:52:45', '', 420, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/420-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(429, 3, '2017-05-17 13:23:16', '2017-05-17 07:53:16', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">The BJP government. has launched the</span> <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=138891"><span style="font-weight: 400;">pilot of e-NAM</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> - the </span><a href="http://www.enam.gov.in/NAM/home/index.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">e-trading platform</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> for the National Agriculture Market, </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">as a first step towards creating a single National Agricultural Market. </span><a href="http://www.enam.gov.in/NAM/home/mandis.html#"><span style="font-weight: 400;">250 markets </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">have been linked to the portal against the target of 220 by March 2017.</span>\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">With the aim of creating a single barrier-free market across India, the NITI Ayog </span><a href="http://agriexchange.apeda.gov.in/news/Newssearch.aspx?newsid=24745"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">rolled out the draft</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> on the model Agricultural Produce Market Committee (APMC)</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">The draft was put for public and stakeholder review, welcoming  comments and suggestions  till March 15, 2017.</span>', 'Evolve a single ''National Agriculture Market''', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '426-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-17 13:23:16', '2017-05-17 07:53:16', '', 426, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/426-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(430, 3, '2017-05-17 13:28:15', '2017-05-17 07:58:15', 'The number of children benefitted under MDMS has reduced from <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=142148">10.8 crores in 2013-14 to 10.2 crore in 2015-16</a>. Funds allocated have gone down from <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=142148">Rs. 12,200 crore in 2013-14 to Rs. 9,700 crore in 2015-16.</a> However, the funding pattern changed from 75:25 between Central and States to 60:40 from April 2015, which influenced the budget data.\r\n\r\nOnly <a href="http://www.dailypioneer.com/todays-newspaper/mid-day-meal-3-cr-kids-go-hungry-as-funds-lie-unspent.html">Rs. 8960 crore has been spent out of an allocation of Rs. 9700 crore</a> in 2016-17. There is a decline in the utilization of the funds, despite the allocation being reduced. Out of 13.2 crore children enrolled in schools, only 10.3 crore are getting benefit under MDMS. Around 3 crore children are still beyond the coverage of MDMS. This information was <a href="http://164.100.47.5/qsearch/qsearch.aspx">presented before the Rajya Sabha </a>on 21st July, 2016.\r\n\r\nThere is a shortage of basic infrastructural facilities and manpower which are crucial for the accomplishment of MDMS, according to a <a href="http://164.100.47.5/newcommittee/reports/EnglishCommittees/Committee%20on%20HRD/283.pdf">Parliamentary Committee Report</a> published in December 2016.', 'Revitalize Mid-day meal scheme (MDMS) in terms of management and delivery', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'revitalize-mid-day-meal-scheme-mdms-in-terms-of-management-and-delivery', '', '', '2017-05-17 13:28:15', '2017-05-17 07:58:15', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=430', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
