(434, 3, '2017-05-17 13:31:19', '2017-05-17 08:01:19', '<a href="https://www.ebasta.in/">E-Basta</a>, an app launched by the BJP government, is an app designed to reduce the burden of school bag of students and provide ease of access from anywhere. More than 1500 school level books are available on E-Basta.\r\n\r\nOnly <a href="http://img.asercentre.org/docs/Publications/ASER%20Reports/ASER%202016/Report%20sections/aser2016-nationalfindings.pdf">20% of schools</a> in India have access to a computer, according to a Pratham report published in 2016. The BJP government has allocated Rs. 311 crores for Computer Aided Learning during the 2016-17.\r\n\r\nNo framework has been published by the BJP government to integrate the app (E-basta) with the existing system.', 'Explore ways to reduce the daily burden of carrying books to school for children using technology', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'explore-ways-to-reduce-the-daily-burden-of-carrying-books-to-school-for-children-using-technology', '', '', '2017-05-17 13:31:19', '2017-05-17 08:01:19', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=434', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
(435, 3, '2017-05-17 13:28:42', '2017-05-17 07:58:42', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">India’s rank in </span><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">‘Ease of Doing Business</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400;">’ improved from </span><a href="http://www.thehindu.com/business/Economy/India-up-one-position-in-WB-ease-of-business-ranking/article16081515.ece"><span style="font-weight: 400;">142nd rank in 2014</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to </span><a href="http://www.doingbusiness.org/rankings"><span style="font-weight: 400;">130th rank in 2016</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, according to World Bank.  This is an improvement of 12 places.  However, on the parameter of ‘</span><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Starting A New Business</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400;">’, India’s rank slipped to </span><a href="http://www.doingbusiness.org/rankings"><span style="font-weight: 400;">155th rank in 2016</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> compared to </span><a href="http://www.business-standard.com/article/economy-policy/india-moves-up-by-just-one-notch-on-world-bank-s-ease-of-doing-business-index-116102501493_1.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">151th rank in 2014</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">On the parameter of ‘</span><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Getting Electricity</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400;">’ , India’s rank has been </span><a href="http://164.100.47.194/Loksabha/Questions/QResult15.aspx?qref=50242&amp;lsno=16"><span style="font-weight: 400;">improved </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">from 137th rank in 2015 to 26th rank in 2016. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">The report has recognized the efforts of getting electricity in Delhi to make it faster and cheaper to obtain an electricity connection.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The government </span><a href="http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/economy/policy/indust