(441, 3, '2017-05-17 13:31:50', '2017-05-17 08:01:50', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">India’s rank has improved to 35th </span><a href="http://lpi.worldbank.org/international/global/2016"><span style="font-weight: 400;">position</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> in Logistics Performance Index (LPI) as compared to 54</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">th</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> in 2014, according to a report by World Bank. It has been improved significantly in two indicators: Customs &amp; Infrastructure. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Indian Cold Chain Industry is </span><a href="http://indiacoldchainshow.com/Cold-Chain-Industry-in-India-A-Report.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">growing at an annual rate</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> of 28% as compared to 23 % in 2013.  BJP government</span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=116240"> <span style="font-weight: 400;">adopted cluster development approach</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to enhance the productivity &amp; competitiveness. Under this scheme (MSE-CDP), common facility centers have been created </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">for testing, training center, raw material depot, effluent treatment, complementing production processes, etc. This has been done to ensure better &amp; productive delivery.</span>', 'Ensure improvement in logistics infrastructure & supply chain management', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'ensure-improvement-in-logistics-infrastructure-supply-chain-management', '', '', '2017-05-18 18:01:15', '2017-05-18 12:31:15', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=441', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
(442, 3, '2017-05-17 13:32:19', '2017-05-17 08:02:19', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">UPA government set up </span><a href="http://www.bihartimes.in/Newsbihar/2013/March/newsbihar07March1.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">GST Network (GSTN)</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to create the IT backbone for GST. Under the BJP government, </span><a href="http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/tech/ites/infosys-bags-rs-1380-crore-contract-to-build-gst-network/articleshow/49049501.cms"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Infosys was given</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> a Rs. 1380 Crore contract to design, develop and maintain the GSTN.</span>\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Out of the 84-85 lakh taxpayers that</span><a href="https://www.bloombergquint.com/gst/2017/04/19/gst-30-lakh-enrolments-pending-58000-taxmen-to-be-trained-gstn-confident-of-july-1-launch"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> need to enrol with GSTN</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, so far 56 lakhs have done so. Out of 60,000 tax officers to be trained, only 2000 have been trained so far. </span><a href="http://www.business-standard.com/article/economy-policy/gstn-enrolment-halts-to-restart-later-117051000096_1.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Beta testing</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> is being carried out currently.</span>', 'A robust IT network will be set up to implement GST', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'a-robust-it-network-will-be-set-up-to-implement-gst', '', '', '2017-05-17 13:32:19', '2017-05-17 08:02:19', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=442', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
(443, 3, '2017-05-17 13:31:19', '2017-05-17 08:01:19', '<a href="https://www.ebasta.in/">E-Basta</a>, an app launched by the BJP government, is an app designed to reduce the burden of school bag of students and provide ease of access from anywhere. More than 1500 school level books are available on E-Basta.\r\n\r\nOnly <a href="http://img.asercentre.org/docs/Publications/ASER%20Reports/ASER%202016/Report%20sections/aser2016-nationalfindings.pdf">20% of schools</a> in India have access to a computer, according to a Pratham report published in 2016. The BJP government has allocated Rs. 311 crores for Computer Aided Learning during the 2016-17.\r\n\r\nNo framework has been published by the BJP government to integrate the app (E-basta) with the existing system.', 'Explore ways to reduce the daily burden of carrying books to school for children using technology', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '434-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-17 13:31:19', '2017-05-17 08:01:19', '', 434, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/434-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
