(470, 3, '2017-05-17 16:45:58', '2017-05-17 11:15:58', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">The </span><a href="https://www.pressreader.com/india/economic-times/20170311/281689729613269"><span style="font-weight: 400;">average delay</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> in grant of environmental clearance is 238 days under BJP government (it was 316 in 2014) as compared to stipulated 105 days, according to March 2017 </span><a href="http://www.cag.gov.in/sites/default/files/audit_report_files/Executive_Summary_Union_Government_Report_39_of_2016.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">CAG Report.</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Only 11% projects have been granted environmental clearances under bounded time. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">A National Regulator to oversee the entire process of grant of Environmental Clearance and monitoring is </span><a href="http://www.cag.gov.in/sites/default/files/audit_report_files/Executive_Summary_Union_Government_Report_39_of_2016.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">yet to be appointed</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> despite directions of the Supreme Court, the report further stated.</span>', 'Decision-making on environment clearances will be made transparent as well as time-bound', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'decision-making-on-environment-clearances-will-be-made-transparent-as-well-as-time-bound', '', '', '2017-05-18 17:57:51', '2017-05-18 12:27:51', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=470', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
