(472, 3, '2017-05-17 16:50:54', '2017-05-17 11:20:54', 'The BJP government <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=146688">launched</a> “<a href="http://www.prashikshak.in/">Prashikshak</a>-a teacher education portal” to strengthen teacher education institutions-DIETs. The <a href="http://www.prashikshak.in/">portal</a> provides the government data to help assess the quality of DIETs. The portal publishes <a href="http://www.prashikshak.in/pages/reports">reports</a> at national, state and institute level which are available to the public.\r\n\r\n12 states in the country have <a href="http://mhrd.gov.in/sites/upload_files/mhrd/files/document-reports/Outcome_16-17.pdf">restructured</a> their SCERTs till April 2016, under a centrally funded scheme.\r\n\r\nThe BJP government constituted “All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE) Review Committee” to restructure and strengthen the AICTE. The report was accepted by the government and <a href="https://www.google.co.in/url?sa=t&amp;rct=j&amp;q=&amp;esrc=s&amp;source=newssearch&amp;cd=4&amp;cad=rja&amp;uact=8&amp;ved=0ahUKEwiA---5vvXTAhXCNo8KHUlRAiIQqQIIKygAMAM&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Findiatoday.intoday.in%2Feducation%2Fstory%2Faicte-recommendations%2F1%2F540356.html&amp;usg=AFQjCNH4HcIgyw7ziNNfQkNh5pf7kLjbQg&amp;sig2=Rxefsl0knzFwNvbR8faTgg">some of the recommendations</a> were implemented. This included setting up of an <a href="http://www.aicte-india.org/prmportal_enu/start.swe?SWECmd=Logoff&amp;SWETS=1494975561696">e-Governance portal</a> to enhance transparency in approval of technical institutions.\r\n\r\nThe <a href="http://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-a-year-on-hrd-niti-aayog-undecided-on-hari-gautam-committee-report-2231963">Hari Gautam committee</a> was set up by the BJP government in 2014 to review the functioning of University Grants Commission (UGC). The committee submitted its report in July 2015, however, no action has been taken by the government to implement the recommendations of the committee. The committee had recommended scrapping of UGC and setting up of a National Higher Education Authority.', 'Rework the work culture of teacher training institutions with a goal to prepare committed & performing teachers', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'rework-the-work-culture-of-teacher-training-institutions-with-a-goal-to-prepare-committed-performing-teachers', '', '', '2017-05-17 16:50:54', '2017-05-17 11:20:54', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=472', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
(473, 3, '2017-05-17 16:47:45', '2017-05-17 11:17:45', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">The BJP government did not set up any Task Force to tackle black money. However, in compliance with a Supreme Court directive, it constituted a Supreme Court  monitored </span><a href="http://www.aljazeera.com/news/asia/2014/05/india-sets-up-team-unearth-black-money-201452895658124791.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Special Investigation Team</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> (SIT) on Black Money.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Till March 2017,the SIT had detected black money worth </span><a href="http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/70k-crore-in-black-money-detected-scappointed-sit/article17397208.ece"><span style="font-weight: 400;">₹70,000 crore</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, which included ₹16,000 crore stashed abroad.</span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">On its recommendation, the BJP government declared cash transactions </span><a href="http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/cash-transaction-limit-slashed-to-rs-2-lakh/article17561911.ece"><span style="font-weight: 400;">above Rs. 2 lakh</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> as illegal. The BJP government however did not accept SIT’s recommendation on</span><a href="https://ilt.taxmann.com/topstories/222330000000008196/cash-transactions-above-rs-3-lakhs-to-be-declared-illegal-and-punishable-sit-on-black-money.aspx"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> limiting cash holding to Rs. 15 lakh</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The</span><a href="http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/10-things-to-know-about-blackmoney-bill/article7194290.ece"> <span style="font-weight: 400;">Undisclosed Foreign Income and Assets (Imposition of Tax) Bill, 2015</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> was enacted, which introduced stringent penalties and enhanced punishment for those with undisclosed income or wealth abroad. It came into effect from July 1, 2015</span>\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Benami Transactions (Prohibition) Act was amended and came into </span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=159882"><span style="font-weight: 400;">force on November 1, 2016</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">An interdepartmental </span><a href="http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/Govt.-sets-up-inter-departmental-task-force-to-crack-down-on-benami-firms/article17286171.ece"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Task Force</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> for a crack-down on Benami transactions was set-up.</span>', 'Set up a Task Force to tackle black money and to recommend amendments to existing laws or enact new laws', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'set-up-a-task-force-to-tackle-black-money-and-to-recommend-amendments-to-existing-laws-or-enact-new-laws', '', '', '2017-05-17 16:47:45', '2017-05-17 11:17:45', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=473', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
