(495, 3, '2017-05-17 16:58:41', '2017-05-17 11:28:41', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">India''s Gross National Savings (as percentage of GDP) continues to decrease from 33% in 2014 to 30% in 2016, reported by </span><a href="https://www.quandl.com/data/ODA/IND_NGSD_NGDP-India-Gross-National-Savings-of-GDP"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Quandl</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. However, there is an </span><a href="http://www.tradingeconomics.com/india/personal-savings"><span style="font-weight: 400;">improvement</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> in the Indian Households Savings from Rs. 22.8 lakh crore in 2014 to Rs. 26.1 lakh crore in 2016. </span>\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Government continued “</span><a href="https://pmjdy.gov.in/about"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Pradhan Mantri jan Dhan Yojana</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">” to have better access &amp; boost savings of Individuals.  A total of 64,400 Crores have been </span><a href="http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/banking/finance/banking/deposits-in-jan-dhan-accounts-rise-to-rs-64250-crore/articleshow/55619794.cms"><span style="font-weight: 400;">deposited</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> as of May 2017.</span>', 'Encourage Savings as an important driver of investment and growth', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'encourage-savings-as-an-important-driver-of-investment-and-growth', '', '', '2017-05-18 13:59:19', '2017-05-18 08:29:19', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=495', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
(496, 3, '2017-05-17 16:58:07', '2017-05-17 11:28:07', 'The BJP government launched <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=155999">“Uchchtar Avishkaar Yojana”</a> in 2016 to promote industry-academia relationships. The project is currently been piloted in IITs. 92 projects have been approved till Jan 2017. A <a href="http://mhrd.gov.in/sites/upload_files/mhrd/files/ru2388.pdf">Council for Industry &amp; Higher Education Collaboration (CIHEC)</a> was also constituted with representatives from both academia and industry.\r\nThe <a href="http://www.aicte-india.org/downloads/Startup%20Policy.pdf">Start-Up Policy</a> formulated by the All India Council for Technical Education promotes student driven start ups by various measure including industry-academia interaction.', 'Institute a mechanism for interaction between industry (including SME), academia & community', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '486-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-17 16:58:07', '2017-05-17 11:28:07', '', 486, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/486-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
