(525, 3, '2017-05-17 17:10:04', '2017-05-17 11:40:04', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">BJP government has </span><a href="http://www.dcmsme.gov.in/Revised%20Guidelines%20on%20ICT.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">revised the guidelines</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> for “Promotion of ICT in MSME sector” under which it has proposed the subsidy of 60%  for using Cloud Computing  for a period of 2 years. Budget </span><a href="http://164.100.47.5/newcommittee/reports/EnglishCommittees/Committee%20on%20Industry/280.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">allocation</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> for this scheme has been reduced from Rs. 18 crore in 2014 to Rs. 5 crores in 2017</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">BJP government </span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/backgrounders.aspx?relid=104383"><span style="font-weight: 400;">continued</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Bar-Code Scheme launched under UPA government to benefit MSMEs for inventory control, wide acceptability of products in the domestic and world markets &amp; higher efficiencies. A total expenditure for this scheme has been </span><a href="http://www.dcmsme.gov.in/schemes/assist_bar_code.htm"><span style="font-weight: 400;">increased</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> from 1.25 crore in 2014 to 1.54 crore in 2016.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Ministry of MSME launched </span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=148729"><span style="font-weight: 400;">MSME Databank Portal</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> in August, 2016 which will provide real time information on various types of the MSMEs registered. This has been done to boost up public procurement.</span>', 'Ensure adoption of IT in MSMEs', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '523-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-17 17:10:04', '2017-05-17 11:40:04', '', 523, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/523-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(526, 3, '2017-05-17 17:11:38', '2017-05-17 11:41:38', 'No steps have been taken by the BJP government towards this direction. <a href="http://www.aicte-india.org/downloads/Yashpal-committee-report.pdf#toolbar=0">Yash Pal committee</a> had recommended that the UGC (University Grants Commission) and AICTE (All India Council for Technical Education) should be combined within a single Higher Education Commission.', 'Restructure UGC into a Higher Education Commission', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'restructure-ugc-into-a-higher-education-commission', '', '', '2017-05-17 17:11:38', '2017-05-17 11:41:38', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=526', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
(527, 3, '2017-05-17 17:11:31', '2017-05-17 11:41:31', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">The BJP government has</span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=116587"> <span style="font-weight: 400;">approved</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> setting up of “</span><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Technology Centre Systems program</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400;">” for MSMEs under which 15 new Technology Development Centers are proposed to be established, and the existing centers are proposed to be upgraded over next six years. The objective of thee centres is to provide support to Electronics Systems Design &amp; Manufacturing.  Construction for 4 such technology centers has been </span><a href="http://msme.gov.in/sites/default/files/Achievments_Brochure_Final__17-05-16_.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">started</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> so far.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">BJP government </span><a href="http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/budget-2015/student/Union-Budget-2015-Rs-150-crore-alloted-for-research-under-Atal-Innovation-Mission/articleshow/46413665.cms"><span style="font-weight: 400;">launched</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Atal Innovation Mission (AIM) in Budget 2015 with an allocation of Rs. 150 crores out of which only </span><a href="http://164.100.47.193/lsscommittee/Finance/16_Finance_48.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Rs. 16.8 crores have been used</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. In Budget 2017-18, allocation for this scheme has been </span><a href="http://164.100.47.193/lsscommittee/Finance/16_Finance_48.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">reduced</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to Rs. 112 crores.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">To promote innovation in MSMEs, 21 out of 80 </span><a href="http://www.pib.nic.in/newsite/mbErel.aspx?relid=133167"><span style="font-weight: 400;">promised</span></a><span style="font-weight: 4