(537, 3, '2017-05-17 17:16:48', '2017-05-17 11:46:48', 'The BJP government’s initiative <a href="https://swayam.gov.in/">SWAYAM</a> is an indigenous developed IT platform that facilitates hosting of all the courses, taught in classrooms from 9th class till post-graduation to be accessed by anyone, anywhere at any time. All the courses are interactive, prepared by the teachers in the country and are available, free of cost to the residents in India. A certificate is offered at the successful completion of the course.  As on 1st May 2017, it has 346 courses.', 'Set up Massive Open Online Courses (MOOC) and virtual classrooms', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'set-up-massive-open-online-courses-mooc-and-virtual-classrooms', '', '', '2017-05-19 01:09:38', '2017-05-18 19:39:38', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=537', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
(538, 3, '2017-05-17 17:16:25', '2017-05-17 11:46:25', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">Government </span><a href="http://dipp.nic.in/English/Schemes/IIUS/IIUS_modified_01August2013.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">continued</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Modified Industrial Infrastructure Upgradation Scheme (MIIUS) under 12th year plan. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Under this Scheme, projects have been </span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=156108"><span style="font-weight: 400;">undertaken to upgrade</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> infrastructure in existing Industrial Parks/ Estates/ Areas. This scheme was </span><a href="http://dipp.nic.in/English/Schemes/IIUS/IIUS_modified_01August2013.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">allocated</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Rs. 1030 crores &amp; the Central assistance of Rs. 513 crores has been </span><a href="http://dipp.nic.in/English/Schemes/IIUS/Progress_2017_18April2017.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">approved</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> under 12th year plan as of  March, 2017 as </span><a href="http://dipp.nic.in/English/Schemes/IIUS/Progress_2017_18April2017.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">compared</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to allocated Rs. 1050 crores &amp; the central assistance of Rs. 378 crores under 11th year plan.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">BJP government  </span><a href="http://www.financialexpress.com/budget/union-budget-2017-infrastructure-status-for-affordable-housing-to-boost-volume-of-construction-activities-experts/532352/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">launched</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">  “Housing for all by 2022” scheme under  Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana (PMAY) </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">to boost affordable housing &amp; creating job potential through it.  While the target has been to construct 2 crore houses by 2022, a total of </span><a