(562, 3, '2017-05-17 18:00:26', '2017-05-17 12:30:26', 'The BJP government launched a television channel dedicated to Farmers (<a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=122039">DD Kisan</a>) in May 2015. Viewership of the channel is around <a href="http://www.indiantelevision.com/television/tv-channels/terrestrial/dd-kisan-viewership-is-72m-a-month-received-rs-800m-govt-funds-for-17-18-170408">73 lakh per month</a> on average. Funds allocated for the channel has increased from<a href="http://www.indiantelevision.com/television/tv-channels/terrestrial/dd-kisan-viewership-is-72m-a-month-received-rs-800m-govt-funds-for-17-18-170408"> Rs. 26 crores in 2014-15 to Rs. 70 crores in 2016-17</a>. The programmes are <a href="http://164.100.47.190/loksabhaquestions/annex/10/AS390.pdf">translated into regional languages</a> by other Doordarshan Kendras.\r\n\r\nHowever, no regional Kisan TV channels have been set up. Hence, region specific information is not delivered to farmers in real time.', 'Explore setting up of regional Kisan TV channels', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'explore-setting-up-of-regional-kisan-tv-channels', '', '', '2017-05-18 12:40:09', '2017-05-18 07:10:09', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=562', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
(563, 3, '2017-05-17 18:00:26', '2017-05-17 12:30:26', 'The BJP government launched a television channel dedicated to Farmers (<a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=122039">DD Kisan</a>) in May 2015. Viewership of the channel is around <a href="http://www.indiantelevision.com/television/tv-channels/terrestrial/dd-kisan-viewership-is-72m-a-month-received-rs-800m-govt-funds-for-17-18-170408">73 lakh per month</a> on average. Funds allocated for the channel has increased from<a href="http://www.indiantelevision.com/television/tv-channels/terrestrial/dd-kisan-viewership-is-72m-a-month-received-rs-800m-govt-funds-for-17-18-170408"> Rs. 26 crores in 2014-15 to Rs. 70 crores in 2016-17</a>. The programmes are <a href="http://164.100.47.190/loksabhaquestions/annex/10/AS390.pdf">translated into regional languages</a> by other Doordarshan Kendras. However, no regional Kisan TV channels have been set up.', 'Explore setting up of regional Kisan TV channels', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '562-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-17 18:00:26', '2017-05-17 12:30:26', '', 562, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/562-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(564, 3, '2017-05-17 18:06:20', '2017-05-17 12:36:20', '<a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=156054">Atal Pension Yojna</a>(APY), launched in 2015, provides for pension ranging from <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=156054">Rs.1000 to Rs. 5000</a> for people from unorganized sector and for farmers above the age of 60 years. Maximum age for registering under the Yojna is 40 years and the pension is paid after the person reaches 60 years of age. A total of <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=156054">38 lakh</a> subscribers have been enrolled under APY with a total pension wealth of <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=156054">Rs. 1350 crore</a> per month.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=136995">Krishi kalyan cess</a>, a 0.5% cess on all taxable services, is designed to finance initiatives relating to improvement of agriculture and welfare of farmers. This was launched by the BJP government in February 2016.\r\n\r\nHowever, farmers suicide continue to rise from <a href="http://www.business-standard.com/article/economy-policy/farmer-suicides-went-up-to-12-360-in-2014-report-115071800758_1.html">11,772 </a>in 2013 to <a href="http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/farmer-suicides-up-42-between-2014-2015/articleshow/56363591.cms">12,602</a> in 2015.', 'Put in place welfare measures for farmers above 60 years of age, small and marginal farmers and farm labours', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'put-in-place-welfare-measures-for-farmers-above-60-years-of-age-small-and-marginal-farmers-and-farm-labours', '', '', '2017-05-18 12:00:23', '2017-05-18 06:30:23', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=564', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
(565, 3, '2017-05-17 18:06:20', '2017-05-17 12:36:20', '<a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=156054">Atal Pension Yojna</a>(APY), launched in 2015, provides for pension ranging from <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=156054">Rs.1000 to Rs. 5000</a> for people from unorganized sector and for farmers above the age of 60 years. Maximum age for registering under the Yojna is 40 years and the pension is paid after the person reaches 60 years of age. A total of <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=156054">38 lakh</a> subscribers have been enrolled under APY with a total pension wealth of <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=156054">Rs. 1350 crore</a> per month.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=136995">Krishi kalyan cess</a>, a 0.5% cess on all taxable services, is designed to finance initiatives relating to improvement of agriculture and welfare of farmers. This was launched by the BJP government in February 2016.\r\n\r\nHowever, 3000 farmers have committed suicide over the past 3 years.', 'Put in place welfare measures for farmers above 60 years of age, small and marginal farmers and farm labours', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '564-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-17 18:06:20', '2017-05-17 12:36:20', '', 564, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/564-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(566, 3, '2017-05-17 18:08:38', '2017-05-17 12:38:38', 'The BJP government published a <a href="http://agricoop.nic.in/sites/default/files/APLM_ACT_LATEST_0.pdf">Model Agricultural Produce and Livestock Marketing </a>(APLM) Act in April 2017. This act is supposed to replace the existing APMC Act, 2003. The states are free to adopt or reject the APLM Act. No state has modeled their respective APMC acts as per the provision of APLM Act, as of May 2017.\r\n\r\nThe <a href="http://www.financialexpress.com/economy/government-aims-to-end-apmc-monopoly-with-new-model-agri-market-law/640612/">new act</a> allows for private sector players to directly buy the produce from the farmers. This is supposed to provide farmers with wider options to sell and to get better prices.\r\n\r\nThe BJP government also launched <a href="http://www.enam.gov.in/NAM/home/index.html">National Agriculture Market (NAM)</a> in to create a unified national market for agricultural commodities. <a href="http://www.governancenow.com/news/regular-story/nam-17-states-have-modified-their-apmc-act">18 (out of 22)</a>  states and UTs modified their APMC Acts to integrate their markets.', 'Reform the Agriculture Produce and Marketing Committee  APMC act', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'reform-the-agriculture-produce-and-marketing-committee-apmc-act', '', '', '2017-05-17 18:08:38', '2017-05-17 12:38:38', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=566', 0, 'promise', '', 0);
