(587, 7, '2017-05-17 21:31:37', '2017-05-17 16:01:37', 'India’s demographic dividend is contingent upon the healthcare and education facilities provided to it. Hence, a coherent National Health Policy becomes crucial. <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=159376">Union Cabinet approved the National Health Policy, 2017</a> in its meeting on March 15<sup>th,</sup> 2017\r\n\r\nThe <a href="http://mohfw.gov.in/showfile.php?lid=4275">policy</a> is comprehensive in its approach and robustly covers all aspects of healthcare. However, some aspects of the policy needs to be discussed and debated. It has set target to achieve a life expectancy of 70 years by 2025, while in 2015 India has a life expectancy of 68.3. The contours of India’s health care delivery majorly depends on its health expenditure.\r\n\r\nThe policy is silent on the measures to increase the health expenditure of government to 2.5% of GDP by 2025.', 'Initiate the New Health Policy', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '585-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-17 21:31:37', '2017-05-17 16:01:37', '', 585, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/585-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(590, 7, '2017-05-17 21:37:56', '2017-05-17 16:07:56', 'A sub-centre is the primary unit of healthcare delivery in India, catering to a population of 3000-5000. Since 2012, the number of sub-centres with no health worker has increased from 3,159 to 5,258 by March 2016, as per the <a href="https://nrhm-mis.nic.in/Pages/RHS2015.aspx?RootFolder=%2FRURAL%20HEALTH%20STATISTICS%2F%28A%29RHS%20-%202016&amp;FolderCTID=0x01200057278FD1EC909F429B03E86C7A7C3F31&amp;View=%7bC50BC181-07BB-4F78-BE6F-FCE916B64253%7d">Rural Health Statistics, 2016</a>.\r\n\r\nPrimary Health Centres (PHCs) has increased from 24,448 in 2013 to <a href="https://nrhm-mis.nic.in/Pages/RHS2015.aspx?RootFolder=%2FRURAL%20HEALTH%20STATISTICS%2F%28A%29RHS%20-%202016&amp;FolderCTID=0x01200057278FD1EC909F429B03E86C7A7C3F31&amp;View=%7bC50BC181-07BB-4F78-BE6F-FCE916B64253%7d">25,354 in the year 2016</a>, an increase of 960. This is a shortfall of more than 4,000 Centres, <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=107152">as per government estimates</a>. The problem gets compounded by the fact that nearly 2,000 PHCs are functioning without any doctor, according to Health Manpower in Rural Areas, HMIS Report,2016\r\n\r\nThere is a clear lack of infrastructure and manpower in healthcare sector in rural areas. Any focus on rural health care delivery needs to start with filling these gaps and shortfalls since 86% of rural population is without health-expenditure support and around <a href="https://scroll.in/pulse/811882/1000-km-journey-and-a-1-5-year-wait-for-a-doctors-appointment-rural-indias-quest-for-healthcare">48% of overnight trips made by rural Indians is made for medical purposes.</a>', 'Focus on Rural Health care delivery.', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'focus-on-rural-health-care-delivery', '', '', '2017-05-17 21:37:56', '2017-05-17 16:07:56', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=590', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
(591, 7, '2017-05-17 21:37:56', '2017-05-17 16:07:56', 'A sub-centre is the primary unit of healthcare delivery in India, catering to a population of 3000-5000. Since 2012, the number of sub-centres with no health worker has increased from 3,159 to 5,258 by March 2016, as per the <a href="https://nrhm-mis.nic.in/Pages/RHS2015.aspx?RootFolder=%2FRURAL%20HEALTH%20STATISTICS%2F%28A%29RHS%20-%202016&amp;FolderCTID=0x01200057278FD1EC909F429B03E86C7A7C3F31&amp;View=%7bC50BC181-07BB-4F78-BE6F-FCE916B64253%7d">Rural Health Statistics, 2016</a>.\r\n\r\nPrimary Health Centres (PHCs) has increased from 24,448 in 2013 to <a href="https://nrhm-mis.nic.in/Pages/RHS2015.aspx?RootFolder=%2FRURAL%20HEALTH%20STATISTICS%2F%28A%29RHS%20-%202016&amp;FolderCTID=0x01200057278FD1EC909F429B03E86C7A7C3F31&amp;View=%7bC50BC181-07BB-4F78-BE6F-FCE916B64253%7d">25,354 in the year 2016</a>, an increase of 960. This is a shortfall of more than 4,000 Centres, <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=107152">as per government estimates</a>. The problem gets compounded by the fact that nearly 2,000 PHCs are functioning without any doctor, according to Health Manpower in Rural Areas, HMIS Report,2016\r\n\r\nThere is a clear lack of infrastructure and manpower in healthcare sector in rural areas. Any focus on rural health care delivery needs to start with filling these gaps and shortfalls since 86% of rural population is without health-expenditure support and around <a href="https://scroll.in/pulse/811882/1000-km-journey-and-a-1-5-year-wait-for-a-doctors-appointment-rural-indias-quest-for-healthcare">48% of overnight trips made by rural Indians is made for medical purposes.</a>', 'Focus on Rural Health care delivery.', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '590-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-17 21:37:56', '2017-05-17 16:07:56', '', 590, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/590-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(592, 7, '2017-05-18 08:07:50', '2017-05-18 02:37:50', 'Little information is available in <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=155854">public domain</a> about the National Programme For Healthcare of Elderly (NPHCE) that UPA government launched in 2010. The programme details are missing from the <a href="http://mohfw.nic.in/WriteReadData/c08032016/78963256452123365785.pdf">Annual Reports of the ministry</a> or its <a href="http://www.mohfw.nic.in/index1.php?lang=1&amp;level=1&amp;sublinkid=6202&amp;lid=4040">website</a>. The last available information is as follows:\r\n\r\nUnder the <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=101931">NPHCE</a>, 8 regional RGCs had been set up by 2014 and another <a href="http://mohfw.nic.in/WriteReadData/c08032016/78963256452123365785.pdf">12 RGCs and 2 National Centres for Ageing</a> were proposed during 12<sup>th</sup> Five-year Plan (2012-17). No further details are available other than the <a href="http://mohfw.nic.in/showfile.php?lid=3730">news of budgetary allocation of 480 crore rupees</a> in 2016.', 'Senior Citizens health care would be a special focus area', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'senior-citizens-health-care-would-be-a-special-focus-area', '', '', '2017-05-18 08:07:50', '2017-05-18 02:37:50', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=592', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
