(597, 7, '2017-05-18 08:11:02', '2017-05-18 02:41:02', 'Ministry of Health and Family Welfare (<a href="http://mohfw.nic.in/showfile.php?lid=3099">M</a><a href="http://mohfw.nic.in/showfile.php?lid=3099">oHFW</a><u>)</u> had put <a href="http://mohfw.nic.in/showfile.php?lid=4000">the c</a><a href="http://mohfw.nic.in/showfile.php?lid=4000">oncept not</a><a href="http://mohfw.nic.in/showfile.php?lid=4000">e</a> on National eHealth Authority (NeHA) on April, 2016. However, <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=154775">no further </a><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=154775">progress</a> has been made. India’s move to notify the Electronic Health Records standards in 2013 was a progress towards digitisation of healthcare. Establishment of a statutory authority, NeHA, could have been a key step to leverage telemedicine and mobile healthcare', 'Set up the ''National eHealth Authority'' to leverage telemedicine and mobile healthcare', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'set-up-the-national-ehealth-authority-to-leverage-telemedicine-and-mobile-healthcare', '', '', '2017-05-18 08:11:02', '2017-05-18 02:41:02', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=597', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
