(603, 7, '2017-05-18 08:14:12', '2017-05-18 02:44:12', 'There is little clarity on the intent of this promise. <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=137143">National Medicinal Plants Board (NMPB) was setup in 2000</a><u>,</u> which is governed by Ministry of Ayurveda, Yoga and Naturopathy, Unani, Siddha and Homoeopathy (AYUSH). No effort has been taken for re-orienting the board.\r\n\r\nThe two schemes which encourage the farming of herbal plants are –\r\n\r\n1.Central Sector Scheme for Conservation, Development and Sustainable Management of Medicinal Plants under NMPB\r\n<ol start="2">\r\n 	<li><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/mbErel.aspx?relid=148832">Centrally Sponsored Scheme of National AYUSH Mission (NAM) has a component on “Medicinal Plants</a>”. Farming of medicinal plants was supported under the Centrally Sponsored Scheme of “National Mission on Medicinal Plants” of NMPB from 2009-2015, before NAM started.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nThe budget allocated to the schemes has remained stagnant at <a href="http://ayush.gov.in/sites/default/files/AYUSH%20ENGLISH%20ANNUAL%20REPORT-2014-15_0.pdf">Rs 70 crores between 2014-15</a> and <a href="http://ayush.gov.in/sites/default/files/ANNUAL%20R%20EPORT%202016-17%20ENGLISH.pdf">2016-17</a>. A virtual market place, e-charak, was launched in August, 2016 to create trade linkages between buyers and sellers of medicinal plants.', 'Re-orientation of herbal plants board to encourage farming of herbal plants', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '601-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-18 08:14:12', '2017-05-18 02:44:12', '', 601, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/601-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(604, 7, '2017-05-18 08:22:52', '2017-05-18 02:52:52', '<a href="http://planningcommission.nic.in/reports/genrep/UHC_ExecSummary.pdf">Universal Health Coverage</a> has been a pipedream for Indian government. <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=106608">A group was constituted in July 2014</a> to prepare a comprehensive background paper for the roll out of the National Health Assurance Mission. There is no information available regarding its progress on health ministry’s website. It doesn’t find any mention in the most recent <a href="http://www.thehindu.com/news/resources/Full-text-of-the-Presidents-address-to-the-joint-session-of-Parliament/article17120888.ece">President’s address</a> to Parliament.\r\n\r\nAs per a <a href="http://planningcommission.nic.in/reports/genrep/rep_uhc0812.pdf">report by Planning Commission</a>, India would have required to spend at least 2.5% of its GDP on health by 2017 to progress in the road towards Universal Health Coverage. However, the <a href="https://thewire.in/24924/health-budget-figures-tell-a-sick-story/">current figure stands at 1.3%.</a>', 'Initiate the ''National Health Assurance Mission''', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'initiate-the-national-health-assurance-mission', '', '', '2017-05-18 08:22:52', '2017-05-18 02:52:52', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=604', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
