(623, 7, '2017-05-18 08:36:50', '2017-05-18 03:06:50', '<a href="https://thewire.in/106575/health-budget-2017-18/">Budgetary allocation to National Rural Health M<u>ission (NRHM)</u></a>, as total percentage of total health budget has fallen from 52.6% in 2015-16 to 43.4% in 2017-18. Under NRHM, the share of ‘Infrastructure maintenance’ has constantly fallen from <a href="https://thewire.in/106575/health-budget-2017-18/">28.5% in 2015-16 to 26% in 2017-18.</a> Low budgetary allocation will impede the progress of modernisation and upgradation of health infrastructure.\r\n\r\nGovernment launched many apps like <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=155854">Swachh Bharat app, ANM Online Application(ANMOL), Kilkari</a>, etc and initiated other digital platforms like <a href="https://www.nhp.gov.in/">National Health Portal</a>, <a href="http://ors.gov.in/index.html">Online Registration System</a>, to bring latest technologies in healthcare sector.', 'Modernize Government hospitals, upgrading infrastructure and latest technologies', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'modernize-government-hospitals-upgrading-infrastructure-and-latest-technologies', '', '', '2017-05-18 13:38:28', '2017-05-18 08:08:28', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=623', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
