(671, 3, '2017-05-18 12:37:30', '2017-05-18 07:07:30', '<a href="http://midh.gov.in/">Mission for Integrated Development of Horticulture (MIDH)</a> was launched by the UPA government to integrate all the schemes on horticulture. National Mission on Horticulture, launched under has been allocated <a href="http://164.100.47.193/lsscommittee/Agriculture/16_Agriculture_35.pdf">Rs. 2300 crores in 2017-18</a>, up from Rs. 1600 crores in 2016-17. However, no data of beneficiaries is available.\r\n\r\nUnder MIDH, <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/erelcontent.aspx?relid=113416">financial assistance</a> is also provided for Beekeeping for pollination and <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=158201">Floriculture</a>. The BJP government increased the FDI limit for Pisciculture, Aquaculture, Apiculture to <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=149381">100% in 2016</a>.\r\n\r\nHowever, the horticulture production of the country rose marginally by 0.3% from <a href="http://164.100.47.190/loksabhaquestions/annex/11/AU3216.pdf">286 million tonnes in 2015-16 to 287 million tonnes in 2016-17</a>.', 'Promote horticulture, floriculture, pisciculture, bee-keeping and poultry for generating jobs and income for rural India', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'promote-horticulture-floriculture-pisciculture-bee-keeping-and-poultry-for-generating-jobs-and-income-for-rural-india', '', '', '2017-05-18 23:25:28', '2017-05-18 17:55:28', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=671', 0, 'promise', '', 1),
