(877, 3, '2017-05-18 23:11:54', '2017-05-18 17:41:54', 'BharatNet (earlier called  National Optical Fibre Network), a project initiated by UPA-II in the year 2011 has been commissioned in 18,039 gram panchayats out of 2.5 lakh gram panchayats. The programme aims to 100 Mbps bandwidth in all Gram Panchayats in the country.\n\nS', 'Focus on increasing the penetration and usage of broadband across the country. Deployment of broadband in every village would be a thrust area', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '720-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-05-18 23:11:54', '2017-05-18 17:41:54', '', 720, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/720-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(878, 3, '2017-05-18 23:12:54', '2017-05-18 17:42:54', 'BharatNet (earlier called  National Optical Fibre Network), a project initiated by UPA-II in the year 2011 has been commissioned in 18,039 gram panchayats out of 2.5 lakh gram panchayats. The programme aims to 100 Mbps bandwidth in all Gram Panchayats in the country.\r\n\r\nSince the project has been commissioned in 7% villages only, it has been classified under "Inadequate Progress" category.', 'Focus on increasing the penetration and usage of broadband across the country. Deployment of broadband in every village would be a thrust area', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '720-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-18 23:12:54', '2017-05-18 17:42:54', '', 720, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/720-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(879, 3, '2017-05-18 23:18:26', '2017-05-18 17:48:26', 'The department of Personnel and Training issued an <a href="http://ccis.nic.in/WriteReadData/CircularPortal/D2/D02rti/1_1_2013-IR-1-A.pdf">office memorandum</a> in October 2014 stating that RTI responses to be uploaded online. This would have been a major breakthrough in reducing huge paper work under RTI by means of providing  it would have However, no website of any ministry has done that. The website of Department of Personnel and training has uploaded only <a href="http://dopt.gov.in/rti/miscellaneous/rti-ques-ans-bank">2 responses</a> on its website.\n\nLand Records Management is another key project aimed at digitisation of government records. Digital India Land Records Modernisation Programme (DILRMP), a UPA-I programme aims to modernize management of land records, minimize scope of land/property disputes, enhance transparency in the land records maintenance system, and facilitate moving eventually towards guaranteed conclusive titles to immovable properties in the country. The BJP government has <a href="http://www.livemint.com/Politics/do9qSSB3siI5VAkM4Pxe4H/Govt-nearly-doubles-budget-for-digitisation-of-land-records.html">doubled the budget </a>of Digital India Land Records Modernisation Programme (DILRMP), a UPA-I programme to modernise computerise land records, and increase transparency.  The programme has seen slow<a href="http://nlrmp.nic.in/faces/rpt/rptCombined.xhtml"> progress</a>.\n\nIn the light of nearly zero progress on the project of digitisation of RTI responses and slow progress on land records management, the performance against this promise has been classified as "Inadequate Progress".', 'Digitization of Government records will be taken up on top priority so that they are easily accessible', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '717-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-05-18 23:18:26', '2017-05-18 17:48:26', '', 717, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/717-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(880, 3, '2017-05-18 23:15:38', '2017-05-18 17:45:38', 'The department of Personnel and Training issued an <a href="http://ccis.nic.in/WriteReadData/CircularPortal/D2/D02rti/1_1_2013-IR-1-A.pdf">office memorandum</a> in October 2014 stating that RTI responses to be uploaded online. However, no website of any ministry has done that. The website of Department of Personnel and training has uploaded only <a href="http://dopt.gov.in/rti/miscellaneous/rti-ques-ans-bank">2 responses</a> on its website.\r\n\r\nLand Records Management is another key project aimed at digitisation of government records. Digital India Land Records Modernisation Programme (DILRMP), a UPA-I programme aims to modernize management of land records, minimize scope of land/property disputes, enhance transparency in the land records maintenance system, and facilitate moving eventually towards guaranteed conclusive titles to immovable properties in the country. The BJP government has <a href="http://www.livemint.com/Politics/do9qSSB3siI5VAkM4Pxe4H/Govt-nearly-doubles-budget-for-digitisation-of-land-records.html">doubled the budget </a>of Digital India Land Records Modernisation Programme (DILRMP), a UPA-I programme to modernise computerise land records, and increase transparency.  The programme has seen slow<a href="http://nlrmp.nic.in/faces/rpt/rptCombined.xhtml"> progress</a>.', 'Digitization of Government records will be taken up on top priority so that they are easily accessible', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '717-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-18 23:15:38', '2017-05-18 17:45:38', '', 717, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/717-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(881, 3, '2017-05-18 23:16:56', '2017-05-18 17:46:56', 'The department of Personnel and Training issued an <a href="http://ccis.nic.in/WriteReadData/CircularPortal/D2/D02rti/1_1_2013-IR-1-A.pdf">office memorandum</a> in October 2014 stating that RTI responses to be uploaded online. However, no website of any ministry has done that. The website of Department of Personnel and training has uploaded only <a href="http://dopt.gov.in/rti/miscellaneous/rti-ques-ans-bank">2 responses</a> on its website.\r\n\r\nLand Records Management is another key project aimed at digitisation of government records. Digital India Land Records Modernisation Programme (DILRMP), a UPA-I programme aims to modernize management of land records, minimize scope of land/property disputes, enhance transparency in the land records maintenance system, and facilitate moving eventually towards guaranteed conclusive titles to immovable properties in the country. The BJP government has <a href="http://www.livemint.com/Politics/do9qSSB3siI5VAkM4Pxe4H/Govt-nearly-doubles-budget-for-digitisation-of-land-records.html">doubled the budget </a>of Digital India Land Records Modernisation Programme (DILRMP), a UPA-I programme to modernise computerise land records, and increase transparency.  The programme has seen slow<a href="http://nlrmp.nic.in/faces/rpt/rptCombined.xhtml"> progress</a>.\r\n\r\nIn the light of nearly zero progress on the project of digitisation of RTI responses and slow progress on land records management, the performance against this promise has been classified as "Inadequate Progress".', 'Digitization of Government records will be taken up on top priority so that they are easily accessible', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '717-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-18 23:16:56', '2017-05-18 17:46:56', '', 717, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/717-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(882, 3, '2017-05-18 23:19:41', '2017-05-18 17:49:41', 'The department of Personnel and Training issued an <a href="http://ccis.nic.in/WriteReadData/CircularPortal/D2/D02rti/1_1_2013-IR-1-A.pdf">office memorandum</a> in October 2014 stating that RTI responses to be uploaded online. This would have been a major breakthrough in reducing huge paper work under RTI by means of providing RTI responses readily on website. It would have also ushered unprecedented levels of transparency. However, more than two and a half years since the memorandum was issued, no website of any ministry has complied. The Department of Personnel and training has uploaded only <a href="http://dopt.gov.in/rti/miscellaneous/rti-ques-ans-bank">2 responses</a> on its website and hence remains in non-compliance of its own memorandum.\r\n\r\nLand Records Management is another key project aimed at digitisation of government records. Digital India Land Records Modernisation Programme (DILRMP), a UPA-I programme aims to modernize management of land records, minimize scope of land/property disputes, enhance transparency in the land records maintenance system, and facilitate moving eventually towards guaranteed conclusive titles to immovable properties in the country. The BJP government has <a href="http://www.livemint.com/Politics/do9qSSB3siI5VAkM4Pxe4H/Govt-nearly-doubles-budget-for-digitisation-of-land-records.html">doubled the budget </a>of Digital India Land Records Modernisation Programme (DILRMP), a UPA-I programme to modernise computerise land records, and increase transparency.  The programme has seen slow<a href="http://nlrmp.nic.in/faces/rpt/rptCombined.xhtml"> progress</a>.\r\n\r\nIn the light of nearly zero progress on the project of digitisation of RTI responses and slow progress on land records management, the performance against this promise has been classified as "Inadequate Progress".', 'Digitization of Government records will be taken up on top priority so that they are easily accessible', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '717-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-18 23:19:41', '2017-05-18 17:49:41', '', 717, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/717-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(883, 3, '2017-05-18 23:22:09', '2017-05-18 17:52:09', 'There is no evidence that establishes any efforts on the part of Government of India to fulfill this promise. Several BJP politicians have issued statements reiterating their stand, however nothing has been initiated by the government.', 'Explore all possibilities within the framework of the constitution to facilitate the construction of the Ram Temple in Ayodhya', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '708-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-18 23:22:09', '2017-05-18 17:52:09', '', 708, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/708-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(884, 4, '2017-05-18 23:24:37', '2017-05-18 17:54:37', '<a href="http://midh.gov.in/">Mission for Integrated Development of Horticulture (MIDH)</a> was launched by the UPA government to integrate all the schemes on horticulture. National Mission on Horticulture has been allocated <a href="http://164.100.47.193/lsscommittee/Agriculture/16_Agriculture_35.pdf">Rs. 2300 crores in 2017-18</a>, up from Rs. 1600 crores in 2016-17. . However, no data of beneficiaries is available.\n\nUnder MIDH, <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/erelcontent.aspx?relid=113416">financial assistance</a> is also provided for Beekeeping for pollination and <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=158201">Floriculture</a>. The BJP government increased the FDI limit for Pisciculture, Aquaculture, Apiculture to <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=149381">100% in 2016</a>.\n\nHowever, the horticulture production of the country rose marginally by 0.3% from <a href="http://164.100.47.190/loksabhaquestions/annex/11/AU3216.pdf">286 million tonnes in 2015-16 to 287 million tonnes in 2016-17</a>.', 'Promote horticulture, floriculture, pisciculture, bee-keeping and poultry for generating jobs and income for rural India', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '671-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-05-18 23:24:37', '2017-05-18 17:54:37', '', 671, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/671-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
