" background_color="#ffffff" body_line_height="2.4em"] [/et_pb_post_slider][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section][et_pb_section bb_built="1" admin_label="section" inner_shadow="off" parallax="off"][et_pb_row admin_label="row"][et_pb_column type="4_4"][et_pb_divider admin_label="Divider" color="#27323a" show_divider="on" height="5" divider_style="solid" divider_position="top" hide_on_mobile="on"] [/et_pb_divider][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][et_pb_row admin_label="row" make_fullwidth="off" use_custom_width="off" width_unit="on" use_custom_gutter="off" allow_player_pause="off" parallax="off" parallax_method="off" make_equal="off" parallax_1="off" parallax_method_1="off" parallax_2="off" parallax_method_2="off"][et_pb_column type="1_2"][et_pb_image admin_label="Image" src="http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Promises-1.png" show_in_lightbox="off" url_new_window="off" animation="left" use_overlay="off" sticky="off" align="left" force_fullwidth="off" always_center_on_mobile="on" use_border_color="off" border_color="#ffffff" border_style="solid"] [/et_pb_image][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="1_2"][et_pb_text admin_label="Text" background_layout="light" text_orientation="left" use_border_color="off" border_color="#ffffff" border_style="solid"]</p><h1>What we do!</h1><p>[/et_pb_text][et_pb_blurb admin_label="Blurb" title="Monitor Government Progress" url_new_window="off" use_icon="on" font_icon="%%160%%" icon_color="#ffffff" use_circle="on" use_circle_border="off" circle_border_color="#2ea3f2" icon_placement="left" animation="top" background_layout="light" text_orientation="center" circle_color="#2ea3f2" use_icon_font_size="off" use_border_color="off" border_color="#ffffff" border_style="solid"]</p><p>Our effort is to enable voters to monitor the performance of their governments. We will also assess if governments adhere to all of their promises in regard to education, health, economy,agriculture, transparency, law and order, minority rights, culture, and many more.</p><p>[/et_pb_blurb][et_pb_blurb admin_label="Blurb" title="Fact-Check Claims" url_new_window="off" use_icon="on" font_icon="%%49%%" icon_color="#ffffff" use_circle="on" use_circle_border="off" circle_border_color="#2ea3f2" icon_placement="left" animation="top" background_layout="light" text_orientation="center" url="Fact checking any statement or claim issued by our elected representatives. No opinion, Only 100% verified Facts" circle_color="#2ea3f2" use_icon_font_size="off" use_border_color="off" border_color="#ffffff" border_style="solid"]</p><p>Fact checking any statement or claim issued by our elected representatives. No opinion, Only 100% verified Facts</p><p>[/et_pb_blurb][et_pb_blurb admin_label="Blurb" title="Discuss &amp; Spread" url_new_window="off" use_icon="on" font_icon="%%222%%" icon_color="#ffffff" use_circle="on" use_circle_border="off" circle_border_color="#2ea3f2" icon_placement="left" animation="top" background_layout="light" text_orientation="center" circle_color="#2ea3f2" use_icon_font_size="off" use_border_color="off" border_color="#ffffff" border_style="solid"]</p><p>Enable community dialogue, and help spread right information to the world.</p><p>[/et_pb_blurb][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section][et_pb_section bb_built="1" admin_label="section" fullwidth="off" specialty="off" inner_shadow="off" parallax="off"][et_pb_row admin_label="row"][et_pb_column type="4_4"][et_pb_divider admin_label="Divider" color="#27323a" show_divider="on" height="30" divider_style="solid" divider_position="top" hide_on_mobile="on"] [/et_pb_divider][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][et_pb_row admin_label="Row"][et_pb_column type="4_4"][et_pb_text admin_label="Text" background_layout="light" text_orientation="center" use_border_color="off" border_color="#ffffff" border_style="solid"]</p><h1>Our Vision!</h1><p>To track every government on every sector by 2020. This is a work in progress and we require your help in tracking the performance of the rest of the state and localgovernments. If you share our love for democracy, please write to us atjoinus@electionpromisestracker.in and will figure out ways of collaboration.</p><p>[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section]</p>', 'Home', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '36-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-05-19 00:28:31', '2017-05-18 18:58:31', '', 36, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/36-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(903, 3, '2017-05-18 23:54:34', '2017-05-18 18:24:34', 'BJP Government has not launched any fresh National Litigation Policy or amended <a href="https://www.google.co.in/url?sa=t&amp;rct=j&amp;q=&amp;esrc=s&amp;source=web&amp;cd=3&amp;cad=rja&amp;uact=8&amp;ved=0ahUKEwi1286j2KjTAhUEw7wKHY8uCsEQFgg2MAI&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.lawmin.nic.in%2Fla%2Fnlp.doc&amp;usg=AFQjCNHs-s6uBfBIPYnj3biLurwu4xBXug&amp;sig2=pV8Ry8S6Izmq6p90-VjnSA">National Litigation Policy, 2010.</a> This is important since nearly half of the litigation in Indian courts involve governments in one way or the other furthering adding to the judicial backlog. An undated <a href="http://lawmin.nic.in/la/status%20note%20on%20nlp.pdf">note from Ministry of law</a> claims that the National Litigation Policy is under consideration.\r\n\r\nHowever, BJP government has not launched any fresh National Litigation Policy or amended it and therefore the performance against this promise has been classified as "Yet to Start"\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Implement the National Litigation Policy in letter and spirit to reduce average pendency time of cases', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '678-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-18 23:54:34', '2017-05-18 18:24:34', '', 678, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/678-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
