(906, 3, '2017-05-18 23:58:32', '2017-05-18 18:28:32', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">No considerable progress has been made with regard to doubling the number of courts and judges in sub-ordinate judiciary. The sanctioned strength of judges in district and sub-ordinate courts has increased from </span><a href="http://supremecourtofindia.nic.in/courtnews/2014_issue_2.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">19,726</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to </span><a href="http://supremecourtofindia.nic.in/courtnews/2016_issue_3.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">21,374,</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> an increase of mere 8% against the promise of 100%. Nearly 2.8 crore cases are pending in district and sub-courts.</span>\r\n\r\nSince there is only marginal improvement in number of judges, the performance against this promise has been classified as "Inadequate Progress"', 'Double the number of courts and judges in the subordinate judiciary in a phased manner', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '367-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-18 23:58:32', '2017-05-18 18:28:32', '', 367, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/367-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
